news.title: Bombay HC halts development of any kind in Bhagwati Greens Phase 2 till Mar 29
news.para: The HC bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Neela Gokhale on Wednesday was surprised at the March 6 MahaRERA order. The association of flat buyers had filed a complaint with MahaRERA, alleging the builder, Bhagwati Developers, had proposed a fourth tower in a "multi-play area".

news.title: Bombay HC advises tenants of 10-year stalled redevelopment project to choose new builder cautiously
news.para: A petition was filed by 44 tenants of Ratilal Mansion CHSL who have been in transit accommodation since 2009. The project was stalled in 2013 after the developer, Orbit Corporation, went into liquidation. At the site is a ground-plus-nine storey incomplete structure.

news.title: Gurugram: Three DTCP teams to check OCs by architects; report in three days
news.para: The teams will consist of assistant town planners and seven junior engineers, officials said on Thursday. They have to verify if the OCs are sound, and submit a report for at least 10% of all OCs granted within three days.

news.title: Piramal to sell DHFL loans to JM Financial ARC
news.para: Piramal Capital had initiated a Swiss Challenge against the ARC's anchor bid, inviting other interested bidders to submit expressions of interest by March 15, with the offer amount required to be a minimum of 10% higher than the base offer of ₹2,550 crore.

news.title: HDFC may contest IL&FS building sale to Brookfield
news.para: NCLAT had turned down HDFC's appeal for a stay on the sale of the property located in the Bandra Kurla Complex, which is regarded as one of the prime locations in Mumbai's business district.

news.title: Court asks CBI to file report in Orris India vs Godrej Properties case
news.para: OIPL has accused Godrej Properties of siphoning off funds from the project to other companies, a claim the latter denies and claims “an attempt to malign our image”.

news.title: Delhi HC dismisses plea by home buyers against loan EMIs without possession of flat
news.para: The petitioners before the court included Supertech Urban Home Buyers Association (SUHA) Foundation, consisting of 123 home buyers, and other similarly placed people who have taken home loans from banks and financial institutions on the basis of subvention scheme.

news.title: Banks can't be converted into builder to ensure completion of real estate project: HC
news.para: The high court said the circulars issued by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) advise banks to appoint auditors to check as to whether there is misutilisation of loans and the banks can only red flag the borrower about misutilisation.

news.title: Will come up with new planning norms: Cuttack development body to Odisha HC
news.para: In an affidavit, CDA planning member Qaisar Iqbal Ali said the consultant had prepared the draft regulation - Cuttack Development Authority (Planning & Building Standards) Regulations - and submitted it on February 8, 2023, for scrutiny.

news.title: China: Yuzhou Group Holdings joins peers in flagging hefty annual losses
news.para: Yuzhou is the latest in a series of Chinese property developers that have flagged hefty losses for 2022, hurt by a combination of plummeting demand for new homes, steep cost jumps and repeated COVID-19 lockdowns.

news.title: SC extends protection from arrest to Ambience Group promoter in money laundering case
news.para: ​The Enforcement Directorate (ED), represented by Additional Solicitor General S V Raju, opposed the grant of relief before a bench headed by Justice B R Gavai saying the person who siphoned off hundreds of crores of rupees should not be granted bail allegedly on fake medical grounds.

news.title: Kolkata: Construction waste plant in Rajarhat to open in April
news.para: According to MMiC overseeing the KMC solid waste management department Debabrata Majumdar, who visited the site on Wednesday, the plant will be operational by the end of April.

news.title: Bengaluru: Come clean on illegal A khata properties, BBMP tells revenue officials
news.para: BBMP has warned of departmental disciplinary action and criminal cases if officials are found guilty of not including illegal A khata properties in their reports intentionally.

news.title: Average hike of 5.38% proposed in collector's guideline in Indore
news.para: In the district evaluation meeting chaired by collector Ilayaraja T, DIG stamp and registrar Balkrishna More presented data to support the proposed hike in the guideline.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC meets 95% of its revised target for property tax levy
news.para: Municipal corporation officials said that while they are confident of meeting the revised estimate, they may not be able to meet the budget estimate for 2023-24 set initially.
